narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: This was my first course in Math Dept. and it was worth it. The most important skill that I developed during the course was learning how to prove things. I was also introduced to the concept of delta-epsilon which changed my life :)

I learned fundamental ideas and methods in mathematical analysis, which strongly enhanced my analytical thinking and mathematical sense. I also found out that Math is such an interesting, powerful subject which appears in almost any subject.
Math? From all the knooks and crannies?

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Strength: covers the basic and most important ideas of mathematical analysis weakness: could give solutions of problem sets to students
It's so hard. I don't understand how math could be so fun and then suddenly this course makes it so hard and confusing yet harder math courses are still ok

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Certainly yes! It provides one with a different worldview and subtleties of mathematics. Anyone using mathematics in their research should take this course.
Yes for any one who wants to get a basic idea of the mathematical world
If you have to as math major, then sure
